label: image data set analysis
definition: The process of deriving a data item from an image data set using computer algorithms. The produced data item can be an image data set, data measurement, or any other data item.

label: raw magnetic resonance image data set reconstruction
definition: A process that transforms raw magnetic resonance image data from an NMR/MRI machine into a reconstructed magnetic resonance image data set.
example of usage: A Fourier transform of raw ""k-space"" data produced into an image data set that represents the anatomical structure of the tissue examined.
term editor: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9676-7377 ""Alexander D. Bartnik""|https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9990-8331 ""Alexander D. Diehl""|https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899 ""William D. input: raw magnetic resonance image data set
output: reconstructed magnetic resonance image data set

label: tandem mass spectrometry analysis
definition source: A mass spectrometry analysis in which the data being analyzed is the result of a tandem mass spectrometry assay.
input: ('data item' and 'is specified output of' some 'tandem mass spectrometry assay')
